(1) @Order(10): ProviderReportMatchRule    ← Match settlement report lines to transactions
         │  @Order(20): SettlementTotalRule        ← Verify settlement net total
         │  @Order(30): UnmatchedOrderRule         ← Orders without payments & vice versa
         │  @Order(40): ExactIdMatchRule           ← Captured payments with no order reference
         │  DuplicateCaptureRule                   ← >1 captured payment for same order
         │  MissingCaptureRule                     ← Payments stuck in AUTHORIZED too long
         │  OrphanRefundRule                       ← Refunds without parent payments



         here i think unmatched order and exact id match both are doing the same job, i dont think there is any diff in
         that , what do you think?



